|Bá
|From Sino-Vietnamese 伯 ''(bá)'' meaning "paternal uncle, father's older brother".
|-
|Bê
|Means "doll" in Vietnamese.
|-
|Bian
|Meaning "secret" in Vietnamese, rarely used as a given name.
|-
|Han
|Means "lively" in Lao, "brave, daring" in Thai and "gesture, style, manner, appearance" in Burmese.
|-
|Hằng
|From Sino-Vietnamese ''姮 (hằng)'' meaning "lady".
|-
|Hương
|From Sino-Vietnamese ''香 (hương)'' meaning "fragrant".
|-
|Lan
|From Sino-Vietnamese 璘 ''(lân)'' meaning "lustre of jade" or 麟 ''(lân)'' referring to the qilin (a mythical creature in Chinese mythology).
|-
|Loan
|From Sino-Vietnamese ''鸞 (loan)'', which refers to a mythological bird.
|-
|Ngọc
|From Sino-Vietnamese ''玉 (ngọc)'' meaning "jade, precious stone, gem".
|-
|Ngọn
|Possibly a variant of Ngọc.
|-
|Nữ
|Means "female, woman" in Vietnamese.
|-
|Tấn
|From Sino-Vietnamese 晉 ''(tấn)'' meaning "advance, increase, promote".
|-
|Tiên
|From Sino-Vietnamese ''仙 (tiên)'' meaning "immortal, transcendent, celestial being, fairy".
|-
|Tuyết
|From Sino-Vietnamese ''雪 (tuyết)'' meaning "snow".
